			<title>ATutor Learning Management System</title>
			<link>https://legacy.idrc.ocadu.ca/37-research-and-development/rad-menu/477-atutor</link>
			<guid isPermaLink="true">https://legacy.idrc.ocadu.ca/37-research-and-development/rad-menu/477-atutor</guid>
			<description><![CDATA[<p><a href="http://www.atutor.ca"><img src="http://atutor.ca/images/AT_Logo_1_sm.png" alt="ATutor Logo" width="153" height="46" border="0" /></a></p>
<p><strong id="atutor"><em>ATutor</em></strong><span>&nbsp;is an Open Source Web-based&nbsp;</span><strong>Learning Management System (LMS)</strong><span>&nbsp;used to develop and deliver online courses. Administrators can install or update ATutor in minutes, develop custom themes to give ATutor a new look, and easily extend its functionality with feature modules. Educators can quickly assemble, package, and redistribute Web-based instructional content, easily import prepackaged content, and conduct their courses online. Students learn in an accessible, adaptive, social learning environment.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p><a href="https://atutor.github.io/atutor">ATutor Details</a> | <a href="https://atutor.github.io/atutor/demo.html">Demos</a> |<a href="https://atutor.github.io/atutor/downloads.html"> Download</a> |<a href="https://atutor.github.io/atutor/docs/index.html"> Documentation</a></p>
<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>
